Name: Khrysothemis Phaidrou
Notes: She forms a marriage line with a Leonides of Melite, an ancestor of Leonid Claudii

Name: Kallikratides Syndromou
Notes: Adopted Oinophilos of Trikorynthos, eventually leading to Tiberius Claudius Oinophilos (Hierophant)

Name: [?] Brother of Ti. Kl. Eukles Sostratou
Klaudia Philippe
Notes: Wife of T. Kl. Sospis (2nd marriage). They Form Leonid-Demostratid Bridge. They sired T. Kl. Lysiades (159), Tib. Kl. Demostratos (160), T. Kl. Leonides (161), Kl. Philippe (162).  First marriage was with an Ephesian. OR Daughter of T. Kl. Sospis & Kl. Philippe, thus of the first generation post alliance bridge

Name: T. Fl. Sophokles T. Fl. Kononos
Ti. Kl. Herodes Attikos Kl. Attikou
L. P[?] Husband of Ael. Lysistrate
Philipe Kl. Demostratou
Notes: Wife of Ti. Kl. Nikoteles (93), mother of Kl. Demostratos (94)

Name: Ail. Praxagoras
Notes: First in the Praxagorid line to hold Daduchy, descended from Themistokles, brother of T. Kl. Lysiades (Lysiades being the second in the Leonid line to hold the daduchy). Paternal grandson of Themistokles

Name: [?] Daughter of Praxagoras Thorikos
Notes: Mother of Aelius Praxagoras

Name: Kl. Themistokles
Notes: Brother to T. Kl. Lysidades, and son to T. Kl. Leonides, founder of Leonid branch

Name: Themistokles Meliteus
Notes: Father of Aelius Praxagoras, son of T. Kl. Themistokles who was brother to T. Kl. Lysiades the Daduch and son to T. Kl. Leonides the daduch

Name: Ail. Kephisodora
Notes: Daughter of Kl. Lysiades

Name: Kl. Lysiades
Notes: Father of Aelia Kephisodora

Name: Praxagora Demostratou
Notes: Daughter of Aeilia Philiste and T. Kl. Demostratos (160). Mother of Xenagoras

Name: T. Kl. Demostratos Sospidou
Notes: This is the Demostratos who was involved in the civil suit against Herodes Atticus before Marus Aurelius

Name: Ail. Philiste Praxagorou
Notes: This is Aelia Philiste who marries T. Kl. Demostratos  (160) and forms Praxagoris-Demostratid branch (with links through Demostratid-Leonid line too)

Name: Ti. Kl. Sospis Lysiadou
Notes: Husband of Kl. Philippe, together they form the Demostratid-Leonid bridge. They sire T. Kl. Lysiades (159), and T. Kl. Demostratos (160), and T. Kl. Leonides (161), and Kl. Philippe (162)

Name: Kl. Themistoklea
Notes: Daughter of Kl. Philippos, daduch

Name: Kl. Philippos
Notes: Daduch

Name: Kl. Menandra
Notes: Daughter of Kl. Philippos, daduch

Name: Daughter of T. Fl. Leosthenes II
P. Ail. Herennia P. Ail. Apolloniou
P. Ail. Dionysios
Notes: Supposed ally of Herodes, involved in litigration in front of Marcus Aurelius about his tenure. He was the one candidate to intervene in the Claudii's tenure.

Name: Ti. Kl. Lysiades Leonidou
Notes: Son of T. Kl. Leonides (154), second Leonid to hold Daduchy

Name: Ti. Kl. Leonides Lysiadou
Notes: Father of  T. Kl Lysidaes (155). Founder of Leonid Line, first to hold the daduchy
